-- Ex-CN Chief Harrison Keen to Run Canadian Pacific, Globe and Mail Reports
-- B y   S e a n   B .   P a s t e r n a k
-- 2012-01-11T12:22:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-11/ex-cn-chief-harrison-keen-to-run-canadian-pacific-globe-and-mail-reports.html
Former  Canadian National Railway Co. (CNR) 
Chief Executive Officer Hunter Harrison said he is “excited”
about the prospect of running rival  Canadian Pacific Railway
Ltd. (CP) , the Globe and Mail reported.  Harrison, 67, has been presented as a candidate for the CEO
post by William Ackman, Canadian Pacific’s largest shareholder.
Harrison spoke to the newspaper in an interview from his home in
Florida.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sean B. Pasternak in Toronto at 
 spasternak@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
David Scanlan at 
 dscanlan@bloomberg.net ;
David Scheer at   dscheer@bloomberg.net . 